<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Confidence & Risk Calibration</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Confidence Paradox</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Players at <span class="text-white font-medium">peak confidence challenge more accurately</span> because they trust their word knowledge. But overconfident players challenge words they haven't seen — costing 5+ points on a failed challenge plus their turn.</p>
</div>

<p>Confidence affects three critical decisions: whether to challenge, whether to play a phoney, and whether to attempt a risky bingo over a safer 30-point play.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Healthy Confidence</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Playing your best move without second-guessing. Challenging words you're 80%+ sure are invalid. Taking calculated risks when behind.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Overconfidence</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Challenging every unfamiliar word. Playing phoneys against experienced opponents. Ignoring defensive needs when ahead.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Focus & Stamina in Tournaments</h2>

<p>Tournament Scrabble demands 5-7 games in a single day, each lasting 45-75 minutes. Mental fatigue is the silent score-killer — you might play brilliantly for 4 games then collapse in round 5.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hydrate and snack:</span> Blood sugar drops destroy focus. Bring water and slow-release snacks (nuts, fruit). Skip the sugar rush — it crashes mid-game.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Reset between rounds:</span> Walk outside for 2 minutes between games. Don't review the previous game — park it and start fresh. Your brain needs the context switch.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Automate early decisions:</span> Know your first-move strategy before the tournament starts. Don't burn mental energy on decisions you can pre-plan (opening words, challenge thresholds, exchange criteria).</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Psychological Tactics (Ethical)</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🧠 Tempo Control</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Playing quickly when ahead puts <span class="text-white font-medium">time pressure on your opponent</span>. They feel rushed, make worse decisions, and can't plan ahead. Conversely, slow deliberate plays when behind signal confidence and deny your opponent momentum.</p>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
    <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Play uncommon words</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid obscure words force opponents to decide: challenge and risk a turn, or let it stand. QI, ZA, and JO are common — try QANAT or TRANQ.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
    <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Vary your speed</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Don't be predictable. Occasionally pause on easy plays — it makes opponents wonder what you're seeing that they're not.</p>
  </div>
</div>

